1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d5 { Boom! Ferguson's Cannon discharges! Lines have opened up! Tension runs high! Chaos and confusion abound! As I've always passionately maintained, one surprisingly effective route to securing victory in chess is to establish an advantage in the psychological domain. With 3...d5, White will almost assuredly be out of book. Dispossessed of the comforts afforded by those familiar positions they've grown accustomed to playing over the years, White will be forced to improvise in dangerous and foreign positions! Doing so with success is not so easy, especially when such positions teem with tactics and require careful calculation to safely navigate. No doubt, White's composure will be distressed upon encountering the enigmatic 3...d5. Consequently, Black will have secured a psychological advantage right from move three, bringing us one step closer to checkmate before a mere semblance of the middlegame can even be detected! } 4. Ne5 { Ne5 is not played often, but isn't a bad move by any means. } 4... Qd6 { I find that this is Black's best option. We force White to make a decision. } 5. d4 { The critical response. White builds pressure on our center, aiming to capitalize on their lead in development in the event that Black slips up. } 5... cxd4 6. Qxd4 Bd7 { Breaking the pin threatens ...Nxd4 and consequently forces the simplification of the position. } 7. Bxc6 Bxc6 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. O-O e5 { If White allows us to conquer the center with tempo, we should seize the opportunity immediately. } 10. Qd3 Rd8 { Supporting the center. } 11. Re1 Ne7 12. Be3 Qd7 { [%cal Bd7a7][%csl Ra7]Covering a7. ...d4 is also fine, but I prefer to keep the tension for now. I'm not too worried about the possible } 13. c3 ( 13. exd5 cxd5 14. Bc5 Ng6 $146 15. Bxf8 Kxf8 { as Black can lob Harry down the board with the support of our rook and has ideas with ...Nf4, ...Qg4, etc. } ) 13... Ng6 $13 { [%cal Bf7f6,Bf6f5,Bf8e7,Be8g8,Bh8f8]Black will quickly develop, castle, and can enjoy a nice central space advantage for the upcoming middlegame. I like our chances in this position. } * 

