10. Ne4 $146 b6 $10 ) 8... a6 9. Bxc6 { Retreating to d3 would leave White's piece coordination in a dismal state, therefore the bishop must be exchanged. } 9... Bxc6 10. d4 cxd4 11. Rxd4 ( 11. Nxd4 $146 { drops a pawn with } 11... Bxg2 ) 11... f6 $1 { [%cal Be7e5]} 12. Nd5 $5 e5 $17 { Once again, this idea proves to furnish Black the advantage! It really doesn't matter that White is ahead in development. Once ...e5 arrives, Black's central control will make it difficult for White to navigate the position. White's tactical aspirations don't even work here: } 13. Nc7+ $2 $146 Kf7 14. Nxa8 $146 exd4 15. Nb6 $146 Bc5 16. Nc4 $146 Ne7 $146 { Black is ahead on development and has an excellent position. } * 

