h ...Nf6 we keep more pieces on the board and drag White into a bizarre and complicated middlegame in which error is almost a certainty. Take note of the fact that 8... Nxe2+ 8.Qxe2 Qxe2 9.Nxe2 Bg4! gives Black a slight advantage, as there is no way for White to prevent us from corrupting their structure with ...Bxf3. There are numerous opportunities for White to slip up after 7...Nxe2+, so this line might be worth experimenting with if 7...Nf6 isn't producing the results you want. } ) 8. Bd3 { Clearing the e-file. } 8... Qb6 { [%cal Bf1e1]A common idea, as will be soon observed. } 9. a4 $1 Bg4 { Most of the time we won't have the opportunity for ...Bg4, but here it works. } 10. a5 Qc6 { [%cal Bg4d1][%csl Rf3]Building pressure on f3. } 11. Nxd4 $1 { [%csl Rb5,Ra4,Rc6,Rd7,Re8][%cal Bd3b5,Ba4e8]The only move we should be concerned about. We should be circumspect about the a4-e8 diagonal with our knight out of commission. } 11... cxd4 { [%cal Bg4d1]Thankfully we still have an attack on White's queen that they need to address. } 12. f3 { Perhaps the most interesting attempt. } ( 12. Bb5 $2 { won't work out in White's favor. } 12... Bxd1 13. Bxc6+ bxc6 14. Nxd1 $146 Nd5 $146 { with a small advantage to Black. We have ...Nb4, ...e5, ...c5, and ...O-O-O all in the cards. } ) ( 12. Ne2 $146 { would be interesting too. Black should anticipate h3 by advancing forth with } 12... e5 { so that } 13. h3 { can be met with } 13... Be6 { , where the bishop won't block in the pawn. The line could continue with: } 14. c3 Bd6 15. cxd4 O-O 16. dxe5 Bxe5 { Black has good chances here. Though up a pawn, White is a bit cramped and will thus be slow to mobilize. Black's rooks will make good use of the files and the bishops are already quite active. } ) 12... Bd7 { Precise. We cannot allow Bb5 to arrive with a pin to the queen. } 13. Ne4 ( 13. Bb5 { is nothing to worry about. } 13... Qc7 14. Bxd7+ Qxd7 15. Ne4 $146 Rc8 $10 { With a roughly equal game. } ) 13... Nd5 { [%cal Bd5b4]Perhaps unexpectedly, White was threatening b4! We reject the trade of knights and eye the b4 square. } 14. Re1 e6 $13 { [%cal Bd5b4,Yf7f5,Yh7h5,Ye8f7,Gf8e7,Ge8g8,Gh8f8,Ye8c8,Ya8d8]Black will have a good game. We have threats of ...Nb4 looming. We could continue with the typical ...Be7 and ...O-O, or if we're feeling aggressive we could go crazy with ...f5, ...Kf7 or ...O-O-O, ...h5, etc. } * 

