f4,Ya7d4,Ya5a6,Ra8b7,Rh8a8,Gb4b3,Gd5b4,Yf7f6,Ye6e5]As it turns out, White's passed pawn isn't a serious threat. Our bishop and rook always cover the promotion square. Once our forces become coordinated White won't be able to defend everything. A game might continue with } 23. a6 Kd7 24. Bd4 f6 { Now the dark squared bishop is free to develop without dropping g7. } 25. a7 Bd6 26. Ra5 Rc8 { It should be clear at this stage that White doesn't have sufficient counterplay and is lost. Their passed pawn has been permanently blockaded and their remaining central and queenside pawns are weaknesses. } 27. Rd1 Nf4 $146 28. Be3 Nxg2 $146 { White's position is falling apart. } * 

