age isn't trivial either. 9....e6 is much simpler and resembles middlegames we've already acquainted ourselves with. } ) 10. a5 { Sending the queen back home. } 10... Qd8 11. d3 { The natural move. } 11... Be7 12. Nxd4 { Other moves we can meet with our typical ideas. For instance, if we see } ( 12. Ne5 $146 { our move is the standard: } 12... Qc7 { With ideas to mount pressure on e5 } 13. Bf1 Bd6 14. f4 O-O $10 { etc. Or, if 12... Be7 12.Bf1 O-O 13.Bf4 Bd7 14.Ne5 Rc8= We just play chess. Another example: 12... Be7 12.Ne4 Bd7 13.a6! Nxe2+! Preempting a possible c3. After we are developed, taking on e2 makes more sense. 13.Qxe2 b6 14.Bf4 O-O with an atypical middlegame ahead. } ) 12... cxd4 13. Ne4 Bd7 $13 { [%cal Yd7c6,Be8g8,Bh8f8,Bd8c7]Black should castle and play along the queenside with ...Bc6, ...Qc7, etc. White is probably ever so slightly better, but it's not at all clear how they're supposed to prove it. } * 

