al Ra6b7][%csl Rc6][%cal Ba1a7,Bb5c6]This is forced, as we cannot allow axb7+ followed by Bxc6+ and Rxa7. } 13. Bd3 { The safest square for the bishop. If instead } ( 13. Bc4 $2 { Black has } 13... b5 $3 { with tempo, and the Black secures the time required to safely dispatch the cornered knight. } ) ( 13. Ra5 { would be a bit clunky. } 13... e5 14. d3 $2 Bd6 { White is on the verge of obtaining a permit to resign. } ) 13... Kb8 14. axb7 ( 14. b4 e5 15. Bb2 { White will try to mobilize their rooks towards our king and will probably be able force a repetition at some point. However, if White doesn't find b4 Black will be significantly better. } ) 14... Kxb7 $13 { [%cal Be7e5][%csl Rc2][%cal Bd4c2,Bc5c4]Black will be up the exchange in a moment and is ahead in development. Still, White has pressure on the queenside and can start to fight back with } * 

