ter } 12... Qxh1+ 13. Ke2 Qxh2 14. Qxb7 Qc7 { followed by a queen trade. In summation, ...a6 legitimizes ...Rc8, which enables our queen to break contact with c6. } ) 12. Rf1 $6 { This is slightly inaccurate. More precise would be the much stronger } ( 12. Ke2 Rc8 13. Nf3 $146 axb5 14. cxb5 Qg4 15. bxc6 Qe4+ 16. Kd2 Qxc6 { but still the position is unclear and sharp. } ) 12... Rc8 $15 { Black has a slight advantage. The game would most likely continue with } 13. Bxc6+ Qxc6 14. Qxc6+ Rxc6 15. f4 Nh6 $146 { White may be more active than Black, but they have several weaknesses that need to be consolidated. Additionally, Black is already up a pawn. } * 

