to target the knight on f4. Naturally, Black should not trade off the knight. } 12... Ne6 $146 { White's bishop cannot return to a3 because ...Ng5 would arrive with deadly force. However, if they insist on going after c5 with } 13. c4 Bd6 14. Be3 { Black can simply repel the bishop with } 14... d4 { and is much better. } ) 12... Bxc5 { [%cal Be8g8,Bh8f8,Bd8d6,Bf6f5]Black is going to get castled and play for ...f5, as usual. } 13. Nxc5 O-O 14. c4 Qd6 15. b4 f5 $19 { [%cal Bf5e4]White is lost. Black has a number of winning ideas. The threat here is If White tries to keep the f-file closed with } 16. a3 $2 ( 16. exd5 { Black can simply charge forth with } 16... e4 { and the file will open up soon. } 17. dxe4 fxe4 18. Nxe4 $146 Qg6 { g2 and the knight are threatened. After } 19. Ng3 $146 { only one move wins. } 19... Bxf3 { White can try to delay their doom with } 20. gxf3 { , but after } 20... Qh6 { there is no defense. } ) 16... fxe4 { opening up the f-file. } 17. dxe4 Nxh3+ $146 18. gxh3 Bxf3 { and White has permission to resign. } * 

