is better because it prevents If we look back to } ( 8... Ne7 $146 9. Nh4 $146 g5 $2 { doesn't work out as well due to } 10. Qh5+ Kd7 { . Since White doesn't have Nh4 after 8...Be6 they are just outright worse. } ) 9. Re1 { [%cal Be1e8,Bf3h4,Rg7g5,Rd1h5,Re6f7][%csl Re8]Throwing this move in changes the calculus. Now Nh4 becomes a formidable idea again. } ( 9. Nh4 $2 $146 { , which would be quite strong otherwise. } 9... g5 { Simply forces the knight back, and after } 10. Nf3 $146 h6 { and Black is just much better. } ) 9... Qd7 { [%cal Be8c8,Ba8d8]Enabling Black to castle, should the center become too dangerous. } 10. Ne2 { [%cal Bc2c3,Bd3d4]Foreshadowing c3 or c4. As mentioned before, An unsound sacrifice to be cognizant of is } ( 10. Nh4 $146 { is much more effective now that the rook is on the e-file. } 10... g5 $2 { doesn't allow Black to hold the advantage here. } 11. Bxg5 fxg5 12. Nf3 $146 O-O-O 13. Nxe5 $146 { White has sufficient compensation for the sacrifice. We should not allow this. } ) ( 10. Nxe5 $2 $146 fxe5 { Black easily has the resources to secure his king and will just end up ahead material. } 11. Qh5+ Bf7 { There's just one trick to be aware of here. } 12. Qxe5+ Qe7 13. Nxd5 $146 { Don't be tempted to take the knight. That will lose the queen. The simple } 13... Qxe5 14. Rxe5+ Kd7 { gives Black all that's needed to convert. White does have three pawns for the piece, but it just isn't enough to hold against both the rooks and bishop pair. } ) 10... Ne7 { As can be observed, Black is in excellent shape after 8...Be6. The following line is one sharp way the position might develop. } 11. c3 Ng6 12. d4 cxd4 13. Nfxd4 { If } ( 13. cxd4 { Black has } 13... e4 14. Nd2 $146 Bd6 { with a moderate edge. } ) 13... Bf7 { Be not tempted by the allures of material! } ( 13... exd4 $2 14. Nxd4 $146 Ne5 $146 15. Nxe6 $146 Qxe6 16. f4 ) 14. Ng3 h5 $17 { [%cal Bg3h5,Bg6e7,Rf7h5][%csl Rh5][%cal Re5d4][%csl Rd4][%cal Be8c8,Ba8d8,Bf8c5,Be8g8,Bh8f8]I adore these sorts of positions. Black has an initiative, the center, the bishop pair, and all sorts of dangerous ideas. Black might even castle into the bare queenside! } * 

[Event "Blast the Rossolimo: Ferguson's Cannon Variation"]
