the reader pay close attention to the upcoming continuations. These positions are exceptionally sharp and perhaps not as easy to navigate as appearance may suggest. } ) 9... Bd6 { Encouraging White to take c6. It should be clear by now that the miserly preservation of material is not on Black's agenda. } 10. Nxc6 $2 Qc7 11. Ncd4 { The only move to save the knight. } 11... O-O 12. d3 { White cannot castle due to the pressure on h2. } ( 12. h3 { prevents ...Bg4, but we can play } 12... Ba6 { Black has an incredible position. It's not easy for White to unravel this mess. For instance, if 13.cxd3 Rfe8+ 14.Be3 Bb4+ Kf1 is forced. If 15.Nd2?? , Black wins. 15...Rxe3+ 16.fxe3? Qg3+ Checkmate is on the horizon. } 13. d3 exd3 ) ( 12. Nb5 $2 $146 { leads to some incredible tactics. You can check them all out here: 1 (See the corresponding variation from the PGN) \- 2 (See the corresponding variation from the PGN) \- 3 (See the corresponding variation from the PGN) } ) 12... Bg4 { Striking on the light squares! While our pawn is on e4 we should always be looking for opportunities to play ...Bg4. } 13. Qd2 { While this does block the bishop in, } ( 13. Ne2 $2 $146 { instead would lead to disaster. White has to remember that for the moment their king is stuck in the center. There's no time to waste moving pieces backwards. } 13... Rfe8 14. d4 $2 { White cannot allow the center to open. } 14... Nd5 $146 { So many tactical opportunities. Almost every line leads to absolute mayhem. } 15. c4 $2 e3 $3 { White is getting crushed here. After } 16. f3 Bf5 17. cxd5 $2 Bc2 { the queen is gone. } ) 13... Rfe8 { White is still unable to castle, yet the king urgently needs to evacuate the center! } 14. Kf1 Be5 $17 { [%cal Ba8d8,Ba7a5,Be4d3][%csl Rh1,Ra1,Rc1]...Be5 prevents White's fork and enables us to get some play for our rook on the d-file. Black is much better. White's development is in a dismal state, their knights are targets, their center is on the verge of collapse, and the king isn't even very safe on f1. Black on the other hand is remarkably active and has a nearly decisive initiative. A small price to pay for only three pawns. } * 

