[%cal Bf7f5,Bh8g8,Bg8g1]A potent rook lift! Black has lots of fun ideas in this rich, complicated position. To illustrate the sorts of positions one can expect from the upcoming middlegame, let's explore a couple continuations. } 11. Qe2 { is probably White's best move here. } 11... f5 { Black now threatens ...cxd4, so White should follow up with } 12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. Nb3 $146 Bd6 14. Bxh6 Be5 { Black's rook now has eyes on h6. White could opt to simplify into an endgame with } 15. Qh5+ Qf7 16. Qxf7+ ( 16. Bc1 $2 Be6 { now Black is much better. In fact, this is just winning. } ) 16... Kxf7 { Both b2 and the bishop are hanging, but if White continues with } * 

