s about as unclear as one would expect. } ) 10... Qa5+ { Black forces White's knight to return to c3 before capturing d4. Once we exchange on d4 we can bring our bishop to b4 to increase the pressure on the knight. } 11. Nc3 cxd4 12. Qxd4 Bb4 13. Bd2 { [%csl Rc3]White holds the queenside together. } 13... O-O 14. O-O Rfd8 15. Qe3 Qe5 $10 { [%cal Bb4d6,Bf6g4,Bh7h5,Bd6h2][%csl Rh2][%cal Bb4c5]This middlegame is imbalanced. Black has enough activity to compensate for the pawn. } * 

