y. White threatens Bxh6 and protects f5 simultaneously. } 12... e4 { Pushing the bishop back. We will take on f5 right away if White allows us to, so they would be wise to capture our knight before it's too late. } 13. Bxh6 Qxh6 14. Qxh6 gxh6 15. Be2 Rb8 $17 { [%cal Be7f6,Bf6a1,Bd7f5]Of course, taking on f5 is acceptable too, but ...Rb8 seems stronger. White doesn't have a simple way of defending the queenside without making further concessions. Black is for choice by far. } * 

