f. Suppose they instead continue with } ( 9. Bg3 { , aiming to go for our rook. } 9... f5 { Black simply ignores their materialistic endeavors and focuses on establishing a dominant position. } 10. Nf7 $2 $146 Qd5 11. Nxh8 $146 g6 12. Nd2 $146 Bh6 { This is already winning. White will be forever imperiled by Black's impressive center. } ) 9... Qxc6 10. Qxd4 f5 $17 { [%cal Ye7e6,Bg8f6,Bf8c5,Ye8f7]Black is simply much better. We are up a pawn and have significant control of the center. Moreover, Stockfish thinks White's best move here is g4!?, which is a clear sign that something has gone very wrong. We can continue with typical moves, such as ...e6, ...Nf6, and ...Bc5. ...Kf7 is a noteworthy defensive resource and may be preferable to castling in some positions, the point being to add a defender to the potentially weak e-pawn once it has advanced to e6. } * 

