1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Nc3 Qe6+ 6. Qe2 Qxe2+ 7. Nxe2 Bd7 8. d4 Nf6 9. dxc5 e6 10. Be3 Nd5 11. Bxc6 { [%cal Ge3d4][%csl Rc5]White intended to keep the extra pawn. As we've learned, this can get extremely risky if White doesn't know what they're doing. } 11... Bxc6 12. Bd4 f6 $1 { [%cal Ge6e5,Gd5b4,Gd5c3,Gd5e3]The key idea is the thematic ...e5 push. } 13. c4 Nb4 14. O-O e5 15. Be3 $2 ( 15. Bc3 { Might have offered White better chances. } 15... Bxc5 16. Rfd1 Na6 $146 17. a3 Ba4 18. Re1 Kf7 $17 { Still, Black would have an advantage. } ) 15... Nc2 16. b4 $4 { This is just desperation. Black took the exchange and was already completely winning. } 16... Nxa1 17. Rxa1 a5 ( 17... O-O-O { Would have been better. The king is best placed on the queenside where White's pawn majority resides. } 18. a4 Bxf3 19. gxf3 f5 20. a5 f4 21. Bc1 Rd3 22. Kg2 Rb3 23. Ba3 Be7 $19 ) 18. b5 Bd7 19. a4 Be6 20. Rc1 Rc8 21. Bd2 Bxc5 22. Bxa5 { White is getting crushed. If Black's tactical vision was a bit stronger he could have easily converted by destroying White's queenside pawn-mass with } 22... Be7 ( 22... Bxc4 { Black can take f2 with a discovery if White captures the bishop. } ) 23. Nd2 O-O 24. Bb6 Bc5 25. Bxc5 Rxc5 26. Nc3 Rd8 27. Nce4 Rcc8 28. c5 f5 29. Ng5 Bf7 30. Nxf7 Kxf7 $2 { Black starts to make some mistakes and ultimately managed to squander his advantage. The game resulted in a draw, but Black was completely winning throughout the middlegame as a consequence of coming prepared with the analysis offered in chapter one! } ( 30... Rxd2 31. Ng5 $146 Rxc5 $19 { This would surely have induced resignation. } 32. Re1 Rcc2 33. Nh3 $146 g5 $19 ) 31. Nf3 Ke6 32. h4 h6 33. c6 bxc6 34. bxc6 Kd6 35. Rd1+ Kxc6 $4 { Black should not have left the e-pawn unattended. } 36. Nxe5+ Kb6 37. Rb1+ Ka6 38. Ng6 Rc4 39. Ne7 Rxh4 40. Nxf5 Rg4 41. Re1 Rd7 42. a5 Ra4 43. Re5 Rxa5 44. Re6+ Kb7 45. Ne3 Ra6 46. Re5 Rf6 47. g3 Rdf7 48. Ng4 Rd6 49. Kg2 Kc7 50. Rc5+ Kd7 $2 { Black walked into a fork and the game unfortunately resulted in a draw. } 51. Ne5+ Ke6 52. Nxf7 Kxf7 53. g4 Rf6 54. Kg3 Kg6 55. f4 Rf8 56. Rc7 Kh7 57. f5 Rf6 58. Kh4 Kg8 59. Kg3 Kh7 60. Kf4 Kg8 61. Rc8+ Kf7 62. g5 hxg5+ 63. Kxg5 Rb6 64. Rc7+ Kg8 65. Rd7 Rb5 66. Kg6 Rb6+ 67. Kg5 Rb5 68. Kg6 Rb8 69. Rd6 Rf8 70. f6 gxf6 71. Rxf6 Rc8 72. Re6 Rb8 73. Rf6 Rc8 74. Rd6 Kf8 75. Rf6+ Ke7 76. Rf7+ Ke8 77. Rf6 Rc7 78. Re6+ Kd7 79. Rf6 Rc6 80. Rxc6 Kxc6 { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. } 1/2-1/2 

