1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Nc3 Qe6+ 6. Be2 Nd4 7. O-O Nf6 { Black patiently holds the tension. We have learned from chapter one that Black has priorities other than that of securing the bishop pair: Developing and securing the king. } 8. Nxd4 cxd4 9. Nb5 Qd7 10. d3 $4 { Whoops! Once again, it is easy to slip up when navigating foreign terrain. Note that White has a rating of over 2200. } 10... a6 { Black did not expect White to err so suddenly and immediately. The knight was already free for the taking! } 11. Na3 b5 $1 12. Bf3 Bb7 13. Bxb7 Qxb7 14. c3 e6 15. Nc2 dxc3 16. bxc3 Be7 17. Ne3 O-O 18. d4 $2 { Another mistake. White's position was not so easy to play, with the two target pawns on the semi-open c and d-files. Advancing was not the solution. Now new positional weaknesses emerge. } 18... Rac8 19. Bd2 Ne4 20. Rc1 Rfd8 21. f3 Nf6 ( 21... Nxd2 $146 { Would have been more accurate. Black's potent rooks are ideally placed. Their influence should be used. } 22. Qxd2 e5 { Everything begins to fall apart now. } 23. d5 Bg5 24. Rcd1 Rc5 $19 { White cannot defend everything. } ) 22. Qb3 Qd7 23. Rfd1 h6 24. Be1 Nh5 ( 24... Nd5 $146 { Black should keep White's forces at bay. } 25. Nxd5 $146 exd5 26. Qc2 Bg5 27. Bd2 Bxd2 28. Qxd2 Rc4 $19 { Black would have had total positional dominance. } ) 25. g3 Qc6 26. d5 exd5 27. Rxd5 $4 { It all starts to crumble now. } 27... Bc5 $1 28. Bf2 Rxd5 ( 28... Bxe3 { Crushing! } 29. Rxd8+ Rxd8 30. Bxe3 Qxf3 31. Bf2 Rd2 32. Rf1 Nf6 $19 $146 { Would have issued White a permit to resign. } ) 29. Nxd5 Bxf2+ 30. Kxf2 Qc5+ 31. Kg2 Re8 32. Rc2 Re1 33. Rf2 Re5 { Time pressure took its toll on both players. } 34. Rd2 Re1 35. Rf2 Re6 36. g4 Qxd5 $1 37. gxh5 ( 37. Qxd5 Nf4+ $146 38. Kg3 Nxd5 $146 39. Rc2 $19 ) 37... Qg5+ 38. Kh1 Re1+ { 0-1 White resigns. That's game. An illustrative example of what often happens when the opposition fails to identify the correct plans early on. White floundered about in a much worse middlegame until the pressure eventually became overwhelming. } 0-1 

